io.spine.server.model.declare

Class MethodSignature<H extends HandlerMethod<?,?,E,?>,E extends io.spine.core.MessageEnvelope<?,?,?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.model.declare.MethodSignature<H,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    H - the type of the handler method
    E - the type of envelope, which is used to invoke the handler method
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommandHandlerSignature, CommandReactionSignature, CommandSubstituteSignature, SubscriberSignature

    public abstract class MethodSignature<H extends HandlerMethod<?,?,E,?>,E extends io.spine.core.MessageEnvelope<?,?,?>>
extends java.lang.Object
    An abstract base of signatures of a handler methods.

    Sets the requirements to meet for the java.lang.reflect.Method in order to be qualified as a Message handler method.

    By extending this base class, descendants define the number of requirements:

    • the method annotation,
    • the specification of method parameters,
    • the set of allowed access modifiers,
    • the set of valid return types,
    • the set of allowed exceptions, that the method declares to throw (empty by default),

      • matches

        public boolean matches(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
                throws SignatureMismatchException
        Checks whether the passed method matches the constraints set by this MethodSignature instance.

        WARN-level mismatches are silently ignored by this method. To obtain a detailed information callees should use match(Method).

        Parameters:
        method - the method to check
        Returns:
        true if there was no ERROR-level mismatches
        Throws:
        SignatureMismatchException - in case of any ERROR-level mismatches
        Implementation Note:
        This method never returns false (rather throwing an exception), because in future the extended diagnostic, based upon signature mismatches found is going to be implemented.

      • skipMethod

        protected boolean skipMethod(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
        Determines, if the given raw method should be skipped as non-matching.

        Such an approach allows to improve performance by skipping the methods, that a priori cannot be qualified as message handler methods, such as methods with no required annotation.

        Parameters:
        method - the method to determine if it should be inspected at all
        Returns:
        true if this method should be walked through further examination, false otherwise

      • doCreate

        public abstract H doCreate(java.lang.reflect.Method method,
                           ParameterSpec<E> parameterSpec)
        Creates the HandlerMethod instance according to the passed raw method and the parameter specification.

        By implementing this method descendants define how the parameter spec is used to fit the Message envelope onto the parameter list during the method invocation.

        This method is designed to NOT perform any matching, but rather create a specific instance of HandlerMethod.

        Parameters:
        method - the raw method to wrap into a HandlerMethod instance being created
        parameterSpec - the specification of method parameters
        Returns:
        new instance of HandlerMethod
